<TITLE> Paturia-Doulatdia ferry service resumes after overnight fog </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajbari, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)Heavy curtains of fog over the Padma and the Padma-Jamuna confluence suspended ferryboat services between Paturia and Doulatdia for about nine hours till 9.00am Monday, BIWTC officials said. Ferryboats loaded with passengers and vehicles had to wait at both Paturia and Doulatdia ferry terminals through the early hours of the morning. Ghyasuddin Patwari, Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation officer on duty at Doulatdia told bdnews24.com: "Ferry services resumed as the heavy fog over the Padma gradually lifted at around nine in the morning." bdnews24.c
